# SecBasis — the 17,950-element size-5 (2,2)-coloured ∅-flag basis (Phase S(-0.4))

Provides the size-5 empty-typed flag basis enumerated by the Rust `flag-algebra`
crate (using the older "Strong density graphs" / `StrongEdgeColouringFlagNoRestrict`
subclass with `RESTRICT_NON_F_EDGES = false`), matching the basis ordering of
`local-flags-certificates/certificates/strong_edge_colouring.{sdpa,cert}` which
advertises "17950 flags".

## Encoding

Each basis element is a (2,2)-coloured graph on 5 vertices, encoded as a
30-bit packed integer (stored as 8 hex chars = 32 bits with two zero
pad-bits):

  * bits 0..19  = 10 edge slots × 2 bits each.
    Edge value (Rust convention): 0 = non-edge, 1 = F_EDGE, 2 = NON_F_EDGE.
    Edge index for (u, v) with u < v is `v*(v-1)/2 + u` (SymNonRefl layout).
  * bits 20..29 = 5 vertex slots × 2 bits each.
    For the GENERAL SEC subclass the only used vertex values are 0 (X = "black")
    and 1 (Y = "red"), so the high bit is always 0.

## CG22 projection

The CG22 universe has `Fin 2` edge and vertex colours. We project as follows:
  * `adj u v`        = (raw edge value > 0)         (any edge type, F or NON_F)
  * `edgeCol u v`    = (raw edge value = 1)         (F_EDGE = 1, else 0)
  * `vertexCol v`    = raw vertex value             (raw ∈ {0,1} here)

